# qC Blocker Extension — Architecture

## What It Does

A Manifest V3 Chrome extension that blocks websites you manually configure during
focus hours. No AI, no hardcoded domain lists — only what you explicitly add gets blocked.
Tracks binge usage per domain and escalates interventions from warnings to hard blocks.

---

## Project Structure

```
qc-blocker/
├── manifest.json              # MV3 config — permissions, scripts, icons
├── background/
│   └── worker.js              # Service worker — all decision logic and storage
├── content/
│   ├── content.js             # Injected into every page — overlays, binge indicator
│   └── overlay.css            # In-page UI with CSS variable theming
├── popup/
│   ├── popup.html             # Toolbar popup markup
│   ├── popup.js               # Status, stats, focus windows, quick-block form
│   └── popup.css              # Popup styles
├── options/
│   ├── options.html           # Full settings page (7 sections with how-to guides)
│   ├── options.js             # All settings logic — charts, rules, whitelist, theme
│   └── options.css            # Settings styles
└── icons/
    ├── icon16.png
    ├── icon48.png
    └── icon128.png
```

---

## Tech Stack

- Vanilla JS — no frameworks, no build step, runs directly in Chrome
- Chrome Extensions API (Manifest V3)
  - chrome.storage.local     — all settings and stats
  - chrome.alarms            — minute tick for pending changes + block expiry cleanup
  - chrome.notifications     — binge warning at 80% threshold
  - chrome.tabs              — tab lifecycle + popup→content messaging
- Web Audio API             — alert sounds (gated behind user gesture)
- Pure SVG                  — all charts (bar, sparkline, donut, radial arcs), no libraries

---

## Entry Points

| File | Trigger |
|------|---------|
| background/worker.js | Registered as service worker; starts on browser open |
| content/content.js | Injected at document_idle on every page load |
| popup/popup.html | Opened when user clicks the extension icon |
| options/options.html | Opened via chrome.runtime.openOptionsPage() |

---

## Component Breakdown

### background/worker.js — The Brain

Owns all decision logic, storage reads/writes, and in-memory state.

Key functions:
- `isWindowActiveNow(w)` — checks time range AND day of week
- `getBlockingWindow(url, focusWindows)` — finds the active window that should block this URL
  respecting per-window `blockedDomains`. Empty list = window blocks nothing.
- `isWhitelisted(url, whitelist)` — hostname-level whitelist check
- `isPathWhitelisted(url, pathWhitelist)` — path-prefix whitelist (e.g. reddit.com/r/ML)
- `getBingeStatus(domain)` — reads stored + in-memory usage, applies 10-min buffer,
  returns {usedSecs, limitSecs, blocked, unblockAt}
- `recordBingeSeconds(domain, secs)` — accumulates in memory, flushes to storage every 5s
- `setEscalationBlock(domain)` — persists stage-3 block until focus window ends
- `isEscalationBlocked(domain)` — checks if domain has an active persisted block
- `clearEscalationBlock(domain)` — removes block when user clicks "Leave This Website"
- `handlePageClassify(tabId, msg)` — main decision pipeline (see Data Flow)
- `advanceStage(tabId)` — increments stage 1→2→3, persists escalation block at stage 3

Alarm tick (every 60s):
- Apply pending binge rule changes (strict mode, when block expires)
- Apply pending focus window changes (strict mode, when window ends)
- Clean up expired escalation blocks

Message handlers:
- CLASSIFY_PAGE, STAGE_ADVANCE, STAGE_RESET, CLEAR_ESCALATION_BLOCK
- BINGE_HEARTBEAT, GET_BINGE_STATUS
- PAUSE_BLOCKING, RESUME_BLOCKING, GET_PAUSE_STATUS
- SET_STRICT_BLOCKING, GET_STRICT_STATUS
- QUEUE_BINGE_CHANGE, QUEUE_FOCUS_WINDOW_CHANGE
- STAT_INCREMENT, ALLOW_ONCE

### content/content.js — The UI Layer

Injected into every page. All chrome.runtime.sendMessage calls wrapped in `safeSend()`
which guards against invalidated extension context errors.

Key responsibilities:
- `classifyCurrentPage()` — sends CLASSIFY_PAGE with URL + title + meta
- `showStage(stage, bingeStatus)` — renders the correct overlay:
    Stage 0  no overlay
    Stage 1  "Focus Check" — Go back / Continue anyway
    Stage 2  "Last Warning" — Go back / I'll take the risk
    Stage 3  Full-page hard block — Leave button, binge countdown if applicable
- `showBingeIndicator(status)` — persistent bottom-left widget, created once and
  updated in-place every second (no DOM flicker)
- `startBingeHeartbeat(url)` — sends BINGE_HEARTBEAT every 1s; triggers stage 3
  within 1s of limit being hit
- RECHECK message listener — clears overlay and re-runs classifyCurrentPage() after 100ms
  (used by popup quick-block to apply rules immediately)
- Theme applied via class on overlay element (adb-theme-midnight etc.)
- SPA navigation — patches history.pushState/replaceState + popstate
- Doomscroll detection — rapid scroll bursts re-trigger classify
- Keyboard shortcut — Escape dismisses stage 1/2

### popup/popup.js — Quick Status + Quick Block

Shows current blocking status, today's stats, focus windows list, and binge usage
for the current tab.

Quick Block section (shown for any http site):
- "⏱ Binge Guard" — inline form: block after (min + sec dropdowns), rolling window
  Minute options filtered to valid range (windowHours × 60 - 10) on open and on change
- "🪟 Focus Window" — inline form: select which window to add domain to
- Both save to chrome.storage.local and send RECHECK to the active tab immediately
- Buttons hidden if domain is already configured in that rule type

### options/options.js — Full Settings

7-section settings page with sidebar navigation.
`chrome.storage.onChanged` drives all re-renders (150ms debounce) — no polling.

Sections:
- Dashboard      — 4 stat cards (interventions, minutes, exited, strict toggle),
                   focus score + streak, donut chart, 30-day sparkline,
                   weekly SVG bar chart, windows summary, binge radial arcs
- Focus Windows  — add/edit/delete with time range, day picker, blocked domains list,
                   strict mode queuing when window is active
- Binge Guard    — add/edit/delete with dropdown selects (min/sec/hr),
                   how-to guide, strict mode toggle + queuing when blocked
- Intervention   — Hard Block or Escalating mode
- Whitelist      — domain and path-level entries, blocked-site protection
- Theme          — 5 themes with live preview on radio change
- Settings       — export/import JSON, reset stats, copy debug info, donation links

---

## Data Flow

```
User visits a page
  └─► content.js: classifyCurrentPage()
        └─► [CLASSIFY_PAGE] ──► worker.js: handlePageClassify()
                ├─ isPathWhitelisted()      → exempt? → stage 0
                ├─ isWhitelisted()          → exempt? → stage 0
                ├─ getBingeStatus()         → blocked? → stage 3
                ├─ isEscalationBlocked()    → blocked? → stage 3 (persisted)
                ├─ allowedOnceTabs?         → stage 0
                ├─ pauseUntil > now?        → stage 0
                ├─ getBlockingWindow()      → no active window? → stage 0
                ├─ domain in blockedDomains?
                │     No  → stage 0 (binge indicator still shown if rule exists)
                │     Yes → start intervention
                └─► mode = hard → stage 3
                    mode = both → stage 1

        └─► content.js: showStage(stage)
                ├─ stage 1: Focus Check
                │     "Continue" → 20s countdown → STAGE_ADVANCE → stage 2
                ├─ stage 2: Last Warning
                │     "Continue" → 20s countdown → STAGE_ADVANCE → stage 3
                │           └─► worker: setEscalationBlock(domain, focusWindows)
                └─ stage 3: Hard block
                      "Leave" → CLEAR_ESCALATION_BLOCK → history.back()

Every 1s while on a tracked domain:
  content.js → [BINGE_HEARTBEAT] → worker: recordBingeSeconds(domain, 1)
    → in-memory accumulator (flushes to storage every 5s)
    → getBingeStatus() → blocked? → push stage 3 immediately

Quick-block from popup:
  popup.js saves rule to storage
  → chrome.tabs.sendMessage(tab.id, { type: 'RECHECK' })
  → content.js: removeOverlay() + classifyCurrentPage() after 100ms

Every 60s (chrome.alarms):
  → clean expired escalation blocks
  → apply pending strict-mode binge rule changes (when block expires)
  → apply pending strict-mode focus window changes (when window ends)
```

---

## Storage Schema

| Key | Type | Description |
|-----|------|-------------|
| `focusWindows` | array | `[{id, enabled, label, start, end, days[], blockedDomains[]}]` |
| `interventionMode` | string | `"hard"` or `"both"` (escalating) |
| `whitelist` | string[] | Always-allowed hostnames |
| `pathWhitelist` | array | `[{pattern, label}]` — path-level exemptions |
| `bingeRules` | array | `[{id, enabled, domain, limitSecs, windowHours}]` |
| `bingeUsage` | object | `{domain: [{ts, secs}]}` — rolling timestamped usage log |
| `strictBlocking` | bool | Lock rules while a block is active |
| `pendingBingeRules` | object | `{domain: {action, rule}}` — queued changes |
| `pendingFocusWindowChanges` | object | `{windowId: {action, window}}` — queued changes |
| `escalationBlocks` | object | `{domain: expiresAt}` — persisted stage-3 blocks |
| `theme` | string | `"default"` / `"midnight"` / `"forest"` / `"crimson"` / `"slate"` |
| `stats` | object | `{"YYYY-MM-DD": {distractingMinutes, interventions, exited}}` |
| `pauseUntil` | number | Unix ms — blocking paused until this time |

---

## Intervention Modes

| Mode | Behaviour |
|------|-----------|
| Hard Block | Jumps straight to stage 3 — full-page lock, no warnings |
| Escalating (default) | Stage 1 → 20s → Stage 2 → 20s → Stage 3 |

Stage 3 is persisted to `escalationBlocks` so page refreshes don't escape the block.
Block expires when the active focus window ends.

---

## Binge Guard Detail

- Usage stored as timestamped entries `{ts, secs}` in `bingeUsage`
- In-memory accumulator (`bingeAccumulator`) batches writes — flushes every 5s
- `getBingeStatus` adds unflushed in-memory seconds to stored total for accuracy
- Effective limit = `limitSecs` capped at `windowHours × 3600 - 600` (10-min buffer)
- At 80% usage → chrome notification fires once per session
- At 100% → hard block; `unblockAt` calculated from oldest entry that would drop usage below limit
- Binge-only sites (not in any focus window block list) get silent timer only — no overlay popup

---

## Strict Blocking

When enabled:
- Binge rules: save/delete/reset locked while domain is blocked → queued in `pendingBingeRules`
- Focus windows: save/delete locked while window is active → queued in `pendingFocusWindowChanges`
- Alarm tick applies queued changes once the block/window expires
- Adding new rules is always allowed
- Toggle visible on Dashboard (always accessible) and in Binge Guard settings
- Both toggles are synced — changing one updates the other

---

## Theming

All colours in `overlay.css`, `options.css`, and `popup.css` use CSS variables.
Theme classes (`adb-theme-midnight` etc.) applied to:
- `#adb-overlay` and `#adb-binge-indicator` in content scripts (loaded from storage on page load)
- `document.documentElement` in options and popup pages

Live preview in Settings → Theme — radio change applies class instantly, no save needed to preview.

---

## Quick Block (Popup)

When the popup opens on any http site:
1. Checks if domain is already in binge rules and/or focus windows
2. Shows "Block This Site" section with domain name
3. Hides buttons for rule types already configured
4. Binge form: min/sec/hr dropdowns matching settings page exactly,
   minute options filtered to valid range (windowHours × 60 - 10) on open and on change
5. Window form: dropdown of all configured focus windows
6. On save: writes to storage + sends RECHECK to active tab
7. Content script receives RECHECK → clears overlay → re-classifies after 100ms
